                            will always be the same.</p>
                        <ul class="features-stack">
                            <li class="feature-item">
                                <div class="feature-icon">
                                    <span data-icon="&#xe031;" class="icon"></span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="feature-content">
                                    <h5>Application stack</h5>
                                    <p>Your entire application will be deployed and orchestrated from your Docker
                                        Compose configuration.</p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="feature-item">
                                <div class="feature-icon">
                                    <span data-icon="&#xe04b;" class="icon"></span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="feature-content">
                                    <h5>Infrastructure independent</h5>
                                    <p>Kubernetes can run everywhere, on your laptop as well as in large-scale
                                        clouds.</p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="feature-item">
                                <div class="feature-icon">
                                    <span data-icon="&#xe04b;" class="icon"></span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="feature-content">
                                    <h5>Bring your own Cluster</h5>
                                    <p>Most of our clients choose to use Kubernetes clusters hosted by Google or Amazon.
                                        As well as getting a highly managed service, they benefit from compliance with
                                        security frameworks such as PCI and ISO27001. If you’d prefer to build and
                                        manage your own Kubernetes platform, we’d be
                                        delighted to introduce you to our partner, Jetstack. </p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>&nbsp;</p>
                        <p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://kubernetes.io/" class="btn btn-ghost btn-small"
